		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We present a graphical model for beat tracking in recorded music. Using a probabilistic graphical model allows us to incorporate local information and global smoothness constraints in a principled manner. We evaluate our model on a set of varied and difficult examples, and achieve impressive results. By using a fast dual-tree algorithm for graphical model inference , our system runs in less time than the duration of the music being processed.</p>
